## Immutable execution graph (unless explicit v571+ / experimental)

- **v562–v570** phase modules under `apps/client/src/ghost/phase*.js` in the **locked subgraph**: no new imports, topology changes, or behavior tweaks without `STABILIZATION` + graph + lock + `validateStabilizationGraph.mjs` updates in one intentional change set.
- **Spec layer is non-authoritative for runtime:** docs do not replace code; CI enforces graph + hash; `validateSpecflowCoherence.mjs` enforces policy-doc wiring only.

## Epistemik sınır

- v567–v570 models **how error / mistrust is scored** inside deterministic rules — not stochastic “oracle truth.” Do not describe the frozen core as probabilistic drift unless code explicitly introduces randomness (it does not in this chain).

## SPECFLOW (every sprint item)

- Tag work: **`CORE-ELIGIBLE`** | **`RESEARCH-ONLY`** | **`FUTURE-PROOF-ONLY`** per [`SPECFLOW_MARKERS.md`](SPECFLOW_MARKERS.md).
- Default for academic formalization: **`RESEARCH-ONLY`** (artifacts in `docs/`, no frozen `phase*.js` edits).

## Multi-observer policy

- Observers (human, Nisa, external LLM, live feeds) **do not** hold execution authority — see [`docs/OBSERVATION_FABRIC_V1.md`](docs/OBSERVATION_FABRIC_V1.md): *Agents may influence interpretation, never execution.*
